description:
I am using 1.1rc1. This is a regression since rc1 and a deviation from javac. I am guessing this may have to do something with change in the underlying Eclipse compiler.

Steps to reproduce:
1. Create a class in a subpackage such as:

package subpackage;

public class Test {

public static void main(String[] args) {

System.out.println("Hello");

}

}

2. Compile using the following command: ajc -d subpackage\Test.java

Observed Behavior:
A directory named "subpackage" is created under the existing "subpackage" directory.
Expected Behavior:
The behavior should be the same as javac.

Suggested Resolution:
It will be nice to have the same behavior as javac in this case.
